.SH "NAME"
XGetExtensionVersion \- query tha version of tha input extension\&.
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.sp
.nf
#include <X11/extensions/XInput\&.h>
.fi
.sp
.nf
XExtensionVersion *XGetExtensionVersion( Display *display,
                                         char *name);
.fi
.sp
.nf
display
       Specifies tha connection ta tha X server\&.
.fi
.sp
.nf
name
       Specifies tha extension ta be queried\&. Da input
       extension name is definedin tha header file XI\&.h\&.
.fi
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.sp
.if n \{\
.RS 4
.\}
.nf
Da XGetExtensionVersion request is deprecated n' should not
be used up in XI2 applications\&. Clients issuin a XGetExtensionVersion
request aint gonna be able ta use XI2 features\&.
.fi
.if n \{\
.RE
.\}
.sp
.if n \{\
.RS 4
.\}
.nf
Da XGetExtensionVersion request queries tha version of tha input
extension, n' returns a XExtensionVersion structure\&. This structure
gotz nuff a major_version n' minor_version number which can be compared
with constants defined up in XI\&.h\&. Right back up in yo muthafuckin ass. Support fo' additionizzle protocol
requests added ta tha input extension afta its initial release
is indicated by a version number correspondin ta tha added
requests\&. Each version gotz nuff all tha protocol requests
contained by previous versions\&.
.fi
.if n \{\
.RE
.\}
.sp
.if n \{\
